<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Portable Charger PCB Project</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">

    <style>
        /* Standalone overrides to fix Vercel rendering for this page specifically */
        :root {
            --bg: #0b1221;
            --accent-blue: #3b82f6;
            --slate-grey: #161e2d;
            --sub-text: #94a3b8;
            --light-text: #f1f5f9;
        }

        body {
            background-color: var(--bg) !important;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            overflow-x: hidden;
            -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        }

        /* Re-asserting the fixed border in case the global link fails */
        body::after {
            content: "";
            position: fixed;
            top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0;
            border: 12px solid #1e293b; 
            pointer-events: none; 
            z-index: 9999;
        }

        /* Ensuring the scroll wrapper works with Vercel's flex handling */
        .scroll-wrapper {
            height: 100vh;
            width: 100%;
            overflow-y: scroll;
            scroll-snap-type: y mandatory;
            scrollbar-width: none; 
            -ms-overflow-style: none;
        }
        .scroll-wrapper::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }

        .project-step {
            min-height: 100vh;
            width: 100%;
            scroll-snap-align: start;
            scroll-snap-stop: always;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            padding: 80px 60px;
            box-sizing: border-box;
            background-color: var(--bg);
        }

        /* Fix for potential heading overlap */
        .centered-title {
            font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
            font-weight: 700;
            color: var(--light-text);
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            text-align: center;
            border-bottom: 2px solid #1e293b;
            padding-bottom: 15px;
        }

        /* Ensure images and splits don't break on mobile */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .project-step { padding: 40px 20px; }
            .image-split { flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; }
            .vertical-line { display: none; }
        }
        /* Force the section to be a vertical stack */
    .challenges-section {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        justify-content: flex-start; /* Start from top to allow room for images below */
        align-items: center;
        padding-top: 100px !important; /* Push down from the 12px border */
        text-align: center;
    }

    /* Keep the text block contained and centered */
    .centered-content-wrapper {
        max-width: 800px;
        width: 100%;
        margin-bottom: 50px; /* Space between text and images */
        z-index: 2;
    }

    .challenges-description {
        margin: 0 auto;
        max-width: 600px;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    /* Ensure images don't float up and overlap text */
    .image-display-container {
        width: 100%;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        gap: 20px;
        flex-wrap: wrap; /* Helps on smaller Vercel viewports */
    }

    /* Force the title to stay centered */
    .centered-title {
        display: block;
        margin-left: auto;
        margin-right: auto;
    }
    </style>

</head>
<body>
   
<section class="project-step challenges-section">
    <a href="javascript:history.back()" class="btn-back-home">
        <span class="arrow">‚Üê</span> Back
    </a>

    <div class="centered-content-wrapper">
        <h1 class="centered-title">PCB Design</h1>
        <p class="challenges-description">
            To create the portable charger, I decided to integrate a TP4056 breakout board and 3v-5v Buck Boost Converter using a custom-designed Battery holder PCB to ensure protection against overcharging and a smooth lithium ion charging experience. Below are renders of the AutoDesk PCB models and physical PCB models.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="challenges-image-grid">
        </div>
</section>

    <div class="divider-container"><hr class="line"></div>

    <section class="image-split">
        <button class="button-img" style="background-image: url('/images/bat-render.png'); background-size: 75%;" ></button>
        <button class="button-img" style="background-image: url('/images/physical-pcb.jpeg'); background-size: contain;" ></button>
    </section>

    <div class="divider-container"><hr class="line"></div>

    <section class="project-step challenges-section">
    <div class="centered-content-wrapper">
        <h1 class="centered-title">Challenges Faced</h1>
        <p class="challenges-description">
            During the creation of the Battery Holder PCB I ran into several problems 
            including IC design in Eagle electronics and manufacturing issues with JLCPCB.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="image-display-container">
        </div>
</section>

    <section class="image-split">
    <div class="nested-vertical-split">
        <button class="button-img" style="background-image: url('/images/jlc-issue.png');">
            <div class="img-overlay">
                <span>JLC Manufacturing Issue: Component Sizing Error and Hole Misplacement</span>
            </div>
        </button>
        
        <hr class="inner-line">
        
        <button class="button-img" style="background-image: url('/images/failed-ic.png');">
            <div class="img-overlay">
                <span>Failed IC Design: Incorrect Pinout and Symbol</span>
            </div>
        </button>
    </div>
    </div>
    <div class="vertical-line"></div>
    <button class="button-img" style="background-image: url('/images/failed-board.png');">
        <div class="img-overlay">
            <span>3D CAD Prototype: Incorrectly Assembled 3D Model of Portable Charger</span>
        </div>
    </button>
</section>
<div class="divider-wrap">
    <div class="horizontal-line"></div>
</div>

<section class="project-step challenges-section">
    <div class="centered-content-wrapper">
        <div class="centered-content-wrapper">
            <h1 class="centered-title">Lessons Learned</h1>
        </div>

    <div class="lessons-flex-container">
        <div class="lesson-card left-wide">
                <h3>Design Iteration</h3>
                <p>Learned that digital simulations (Eagle/Fusion) rarely account for physical manufacturing tolerances. Iterating early saved weeks of debugging.</p>
        </div>
            
    <div class="lesson-card right-wide">
                <h3>Supply Chain</h3>
                <p>Navigating JLCPCB's manufacturing capabilities taught me to design for "DFM" (Design for Manufacturability) rather than just theoretical perfection.</p>
        </div>

    <div class="lesson-card full-width">
                <h3>Thermal Management</h3>
                <p>Discovered the importance of copper pours to dissipate heat from the Buck-Boost converter under high iPhone charging loads.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
</body>
</html>